<subSubSection box="[132,232,630,656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[132,776,630,720]" box="[132,232,630,656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">REMARKS</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="296" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[132,776,630,720]" lastBlockId="7.[810,1457,215,719]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" box="[132,310,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis box="[132,310,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" box="[588,772,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis box="[588,772,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by thecongested-cymose inflorescences,short peduncles, slenderly salverform corollas and subglobose capsules, but differs from the latter mainly by having erect stems (vs ascending), most plant parts glabrous or subglabrous (vs densely pubescent), leaf blades narrowly elliptic-oblong or elliptic-oblong(vs ovate to ovate-elliptic) and calyx lobes 
<quantity box="[968,1071,343,369]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.7">1.7-3 mm</quantity>
long (vs 
<quantity box="[1159,1282,343,370]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="3.5">3.5-4.5 mm</quantity>
long) (
<bibRefCitation author="LO H. S." box="[1353,1440,343,369]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="31 - 53" refId="ref2995" refString="LO H. S. 1986. - Materials for Chinese Rubiaceae (I). Bulletin of Botanical Research, Harbin 6 (4): 31 - 53." type="journal article" year="1986">Lo 1986</bibRefCitation>
). Currently, there are five species of 
<taxonomicName authority="BLUME" box="[1202,1305,375,401]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1202,1305,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distributed in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[910,1000,406,432]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LO H. S." box="[1011,1098,407,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="86 - 110" refId="ref3026" refString="LO H. S. 1999. - Spiradiclis Blume, in LO H. S. (ed.), Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae. Vol. 71 (1). Science Press, Beijing: 86 - 110." type="book chapter" year="1999">Lo 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="HO P. H." box="[1108,1202,407,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" refId="ref2901" refString="HO P. H. 2000. - An Illustrated Flora of Vietnam. Vol. 3. Tr e Publishing House, Ho Chi Minh City, 1020 p." type="book" year="2000">Hô 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="LEE J. K. &amp; KHANG N. S. &amp; CHOUDHARY R. K. &amp; QUANG B. H." box="[1213,1358,406,433]" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" pagination="645 - 651" refId="ref2932" refString="LEE J. K., KHANG N. S., CHOUDHARY R. K. &amp; QUANG B. H. 2019. - Two new records of Spiradiclis (Rubiaceae) from Vietnam. Korean Journal of Agricultural Science 46 (3): 645 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.7744 / kjoas. 20190051" type="journal article" year="2019">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[1253,1301,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Among them, 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" box="[882,1071,438,464]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis box="[882,1071,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Pit" box="[1086,1223,438,465]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptobotrya">
<emphasis box="[1086,1223,438,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. leptobotrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are restricted to limestone karst areas and usually occur at elevations of 
<quantity box="[949,1069,502,529]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="450.0" valueMax="600.0" valueMin="300.0">300-600 m</quantity>
, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume" box="[1142,1262,503,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[1142,1262,503,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" box="[1314,1456,502,529]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[1314,1456,502,529]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
grow on slightly acidic soil at elevations of 
<quantity box="[1263,1409,534,561]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="2700.0" valueMax="2900.0" valueMin="2500.0">2500-2900 m</quantity>
and 
<quantity box="[814,921,566,593]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" unit="m" value="600.0" valueMax="1200.0" valueMin="0.0">0-1200 m</quantity>
, respectively. Additionally, the flowering time of the genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[906,996,598,624]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
is concentrated in May (
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" box="[1253,1393,598,624]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis box="[1253,1393,598,624]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), July (
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" box="[821,921,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coccinea">
<emphasis box="[821,921,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. coccinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), September (
<taxonomicName authority="Blume" box="[1059,1173,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[1059,1173,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="H. S. Lo" box="[1218,1404,630,656]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="purpureocaerulea">
<emphasis box="[1218,1404,630,656]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S.purpureocaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and December (
<taxonomicName authority="Pit" box="[933,1065,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptobotrya">
<emphasis box="[933,1065,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">S. leptobotrya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). A key to the five species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume" box="[1354,1456,662,688]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="296" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1354,1456,662,688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Spiradiclis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[839,929,693,719]" name="Vietnam" pageId="7" pageNumber="296">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
is provided below.
</paragraph>
